3. The Flight Check System (Explained)
You asked for an explanation of this. The Flight Check replaces bulleted lists for strategies or next steps.
The Philosophy: Standard consultants give "Advice." Architects give "Protocols." Advice is read; Protocols are executed.
The Visual: Imagine a pre-flight checklist in a cockpit.
• Structure: A vertical stack of slim, horizontal glass bars.
• Left Side: A status indicator (Empty Circle = Pending, Check = Done).
• Center: The instruction (e.g., "Request Interval Data from Oncor").
• Right Side: A "Copy" or "Execute" vector icon.
The Interaction: When the AI suggests: "1. Email the CFO. 2. Pull the 4CP report." It renders as interactive rows. You can click a row to:
1. Copy the text to your clipboard.
2. Send it to your "Tasks" list [Source 317, 880].

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. New Capabilities (Based on GEMINI_CAPABILITIES.md)
I have analyzed your capabilities file [Source 317, 323, 324]. Here are three additional forensic upgrades to maximize the "Premium Feel."
A. The "Evidence Locker" (Document Preview)
• Current Capability: list_account_documents.
• The Upgrade: Do not just list filenames. Render a Grid of Glass Tiles.
    ◦ Visual: A small PDF icon (red/white) inside a glass square.
    ◦ Metadata: Filename (truncated) and Date.
    ◦ Action: Hovering over the tile shows a "Download" or "Analyze" button. This connects directly to your Bill Debugger [Source 1185].
B. The "Scarcity Gauge" (Risk Visualization)
• Current Capability: get_energy_news and market intelligence [Source 318].
• The Upgrade: When you ask about grid status, render a "Voltage Bar."
    ◦ Visual: A horizontal gradient bar.
    ◦ Left (Green): Stable.
    ◦ Right (Red): Scarcity (Price Caps).
    ◦ Indicator: A glowing white needle showing the current ERCOT reserve margin [Source 895].
    ◦ Why: It visualizes "Physics" rather than just telling you the price.
C. The "Conversation Snippet" (Deep Search)
• Current Capability: search_interactions (scans call transcripts) [Source 317, 319].
• The Upgrade: When you search "Did Billy mention a contract end date?", do not just say "Yes."
    ◦ Render: A "Waveform Card."
    ◦ Visual: A visual audio wave representation.
    ◦ Text: The specific 2 sentences from the transcript where the keyword appears, highlighted in Klein Blue.
    ◦ Context: "Call with Billy Ragland • Oct 14, 2025" [Source 200].
Implementation Plan
1. Update chat.tsx: Add renderers for identity_card, flight_check, and evidence_grid.
2. Update GEMINI_CAPABILITIES.md: Instruct the AI to output these specific JSON structures instead of markdown lists.
3. Style: Apply the font-mono tabular-nums class to all numbers inside these new components to maintain the forensic aesthetic.